highly_rated_on_rotten_tomatoes.title: Highly Rated on Rotten Tomatoes
highly_rated_on_rotten_tomatoes.description: Movies that have gotten the seal of approval from viewers and critics on Rotten Tomatoes.

65291.title: XXY
65291.description: When an intersex teenager comes of age, she asks difficult questions about her gender identity and makes a decision that will impact her future.

255739.title: A Monster in Paris
255739.description: Experiments gone wrong and a chemical explosion results in a monster unleashed in Paris, but he might not be as dangerous as everyone thought.

257360.title: Sleepaway Camp
257360.description: Following the death of her family, Angela is sent to a camp for the summer. After her arrival, brutal accidents begin to kill the other campers.

289816.title: Ghost In The Shell
289816.description: See the groundbreaking original before the release of the live-action remake starring Scarlett Johansson! It is 2029 and a female cyborg hunts a hacker who robs humans of their memories.

294338.title: Lourdes
294338.description: In order to escape her isolation, wheelchair-bound Christine makes a life changing journey to Lourdes, the iconic site of pilgrimage in the Pyrenees Mountains.

299580.title: The Big Easy
299580.description: A new female district attorney is unhappy with the gangs and corruption in New Orleans and bonds with a detective in this sultry crime thriller.

300173.title: Pumping Iron
300173.description: Arnold Schwarzenegger and Lou Ferrigno face off in a no-holds-barred competition for the title of Mr. Olympia in this critically-acclaimed film.

300449.title: Eight Men Out
300449.description: A dramatization about the infamous 1919 "Black Sox Scandal," in which eight members of the Chicago White Sox conspired with gamblers to throw the World Series in return for cash.

302708.title: The Long Goodbye
302708.description: In this neo-noir thriller, a private detective is determined to solve a difficult case after he becomes a suspect in the murder of his friend’s wife.

306935.title: Lars and The Real Girl
306935.description: A delusional young man strikes up an unconventional relationship with a doll he finds on the Internet in this weird and warm comedy.

306938.title: Of Mice and Men
306938.description: In this adaptation of John Steinbeck's classic novel, a migrant worker looks after his dimwitted, gentle-giant friend during the Great Depression.

307749.title: Blue Steel
307749.description: A rookie New York cop must deal with more than she bargained for, including a misconduct charge and a psychopath who's become obsessed with her.

310149.title: The Secret of NIMH
310149.description: In this animated adventure, a timid mouse seeks help from a colony of intelligent rats to save her family, but the rats have their own problems.

310154.title: 12 Angry Men
310154.description: A twelve-person jury becomes increasingly tense with arguments continuing into the night as one juror must convince the other eleven he is right.

312175.title: Dirty Rotten Scoundrels
312175.description: Who will emerge as the ultimate hustler when a sophisticated con man and a free-wheeling huckster compete to scam an heiress out of $50,000?

312184.title: The Last Waltz
312184.description: This classic concert documentary focuses on The Band’s farewell concert in San Francisco, where they are joined by a number of special musical guests.

314069.title: The Rape of Europa
314069.description: In a journey through seven countries, this film explores the violent whirlwind of Nazism that threatened to wipe out the artistic heritage of Europe.

316454.title: Secretary
316454.description: Hoping to recover from her troubled past, a socially awkward woman becomes a secretary for an eccentric lawyer who is aroused by her obedience.

321856.title: The Blair Witch Project
321856.description: A trio of filmmakers trek to uncover an urban legend, becomes an excursion into heart-stopping terror, in the original "found footage" horror.

326245.title: Dial M For Murder
326245.description: When an ex-tennis pro’s plan to murder his cheating wife and steal her inheritance goes awry, he must find a way to evade the law.

326260.title: Suspiria
326260.description: A series of gruesome murders and inexplicable events lead a new student to suspect something evil is at play at a prestigious ballet academy.

334159.title: The Return of the Living Dead
334159.description: While working at a medical supply company, two employees release a gas that raises the dead, causing the town to be overrun with flesh-eating zombies.

348456.title: The Good, the Bad and the Ugly
348456.description: Clint Eastwood portrays the invincible "Man With No Name" in a lethal pursuit of $200,000 in Confederate money.  Lee Van Cleef and Eli Wallach also star in this renowned western.

356528.title: Bowling for Columbine
356528.description: This documentary examines gun violence in the U.S. in relation to other countries, including the specific events that led to the Columbine massacre.

356529.title: A Fish Called Wanda
356529.description: After pulling off a diamond heist, the motley crew of culprits dupe one another repeatedly in hopes of pocketing the loot, in this black comedy.

358570.title: Bubba Ho-Tep
358570.description: An aging Elvis joins forces with a fellow nursing home resident who believes he's JFK to fight a mummy who wants to steal the souls of the elderly.

369730.title: Igby Goes Down
369730.description: Born into privilege, a rebellious teenager longs for a life far from his schizophrenic father, self-absorbed mother, and conservative big brother.

371078.title: A Most Wanted Man
371078.description: When a mysterious immigrant arrives in Hamburg, he attracts the attention of U.S. and German intelligence, kicking off a race to uncover the truth.

376133.title: Teeth
376133.description: During a traumatic assault, a repressed teen finds out her vagina has protective teeth and uses this discovery as a source of empowerment and revenge.

389503.title: Robocop
389503.description: A cop who died in the line of duty is transformed into a chrome-plated cyborg policeman with an indestructible new body and a thirst for revenge.

400849.title: Sunshine Cleaning
400849.description: A once-popular single mother-turned-maid gets a new lease on life when she gets into the lucrative world of crime scene cleanup with her sister’s help.

400850.title: Meatballs
400850.description: In this classic comedy, camp counselor Tripper guides a collection of lovable campers and libidinous staff through the pleasures of a coed summer,

401466.title: Four Weddings and a Funeral
401466.description: An Englishman meets an American woman at a wedding, but his inability to express his feelings forestalls any chance at love, until they meet again...and again.

404623.title: Battle Royale
404623.description: A group of students from a Japanese high school are forced to compete in a battle, killing one another until only one is left standing.

405451.title: Rescue Dawn
405451.description: Based on the true story of a captured German-American fighter pilot in the Vietnam War who plans a daring escape after suffering abuse by his captors.

417716.title: Buffalo 66
417716.description: Billy Brown just got out of jail. Now he’s going to serve some real time. He’s going home.

438040.title: The World's Fastest Indian
438040.description: An eccentric racer takes his custom-built motorcycle to America with hopes of setting the world land-speed record in this inspiring true story.

438042.title: Goon
438042.description: A bouncer looking for purpose takes his fighting skills to the hockey rink where his epic brawls could make him a star—if he can learn how to skate.

439502.title: Europa Report
439502.description: Six astronauts travel to Jupiter's moon Europa to search for life beneath its surface, and make a shocking discovery, in this found-footage thriller.

439506.title: Blackthorn
439506.description: Living under an alias in exile, Butch Cassidy gets homesick, but before he can quit Bolivia, a young robber thrusts him into one last mad adventure.

441470.title: Super Size Me
441470.description: Documentarian Morgan Spurlock explores the consequences on his health of a one-month diet consisting solely of items from the McDonald's menu.

448257.title: Amores Perros
448257.description: A horrific car accident connects the lives of three strangers: a lovesick dog fighter, an injured supermodel and a hitman running from his past.

448663.title: Leaving Las Vegas
448663.description: Determined to end it all, a committed drinker picks Vegas as his last stop, but he finds comfort with a kind prostitute who needs help of her own.

456876.title: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call New Orleans
456876.description: In the wake of Hurricane Katrina, a detective investigates the murders of several Senegalese immigrants.

456902.title: Trust
456902.description: When an adolescent girl meets her first boyfriend online, he turns out to be a sexual predator who tears the life of her happy suburban family apart.

460204.title: King of New York
460204.description: A New York drug lord just released from prison is determined to rule the streets again with a vengeance in this gritty action film.

460877.title: Blue Ruin
460877.description: Pushed to his limits, a man returns home to Virginia in search of bloody vengeance, but he becomes embroiled in a battle with a dangerous family.

462517.title: The Illusionist
462517.description: In 19th century Vienna, a magician uses his talents to win the love of a noble woman but makes an enemy of the Crown Prince, now his romantic rival.

462800.title: Enron: the Smartest Guys in the Room
462800.description: The rise and fall of Enron is the focus as executives got rich pretending the company was more profitable while lower-level employees lost everything.

465170.title: Goodnight Mommy
465170.description: Young twin brothers vow to protect each other when their mother comes home with her face obscured by bandages, which makes them question her identity.

466212.title: Submarine
466212.description: A teenage boy aims to fulfill two dreams: to lose his virginity by his 16th birthday and to extinguish the flame between his mom and her ex-lover.

466619.title: Married to the Mob
466619.description: Living a normal life isn't easy for a mobster's widow when she attracts the attention of an enamored FBI agent and a married Mafioso.

467545.title: The Grandmaster

474070.title: We Are What We Are
474070.description: A reclusive family, who secretly follow ancient customs, risk exposure in their town as a torrential storm forces the daughters into survival mode.

475822.title: Departures
475822.description: Foreign Language Oscar-winner about a recently unemployed cellist musician who ends up taking a job preparing the dead for their funerals.

475898.title: Heathers
475898.description: When a snobbish high school clique threatens to ruin her reputation, a teenage girl teams up with a sociopath and plots to kill the cool kids.

479943.title: Rampart
479943.description: When LA's Rampart division gets caught up in a police corruption scandal, a veteran cop with a reputation becomes a target.

480284.title: Bernie
480284.description: When a lovable mortician in a Texas town gets involved with a rich, nasty widow, she tightens her grip and steers him on a course toward a murder rap.

480291.title: Triangle
480291.description: A woman's yacht trip turns to terror when she hits a storm in and her group is forced to board a seemingly deserted ocean liner to get to safety.

487757.title: Monster
487757.description: This true story of a woman with a tortured past traces her path from prostitution, to hopeful love, to vengeful murder, to becoming a serial killer.

491807.title: Ginger Snaps
491807.description: Although they’re obsessed with death, two sisters are not prepared to handle when one of them is bitten by a werewolf, in this coming-of-age drama.

499404.title: The Texas Chain Saw Massacre
499404.description: After a run-in with a group of cannibals, a young woman and her friends are terrorized by Leatherface and his chainsaw  in this classic slasher.

499465.title: Housebound
499465.description: A violent young woman and felon gets placed on house arrest, but prison would be safer for her than what becomes a halfway house of paranormal horror.

504160.title: Better Watch Out
504160.description: In this holiday horror farce, a babysitter must hold the fort and protect a 12-year-old boy during an increasingly bizarre home invasion.

505253.description: For a high school dropout and his slacker friend, trafficking marijuana across the Canadian border seems like the perfect scheme...until it’s not.

505980.title: A Pigeon Sat on a Branch Reflecting on Existence

506145.description: A policeman races against time to save his daughter from a mysterious sickness spreading through a small village.

507469.title: August: Osage County
507469.description: A dysfunctional mother’s emotional wounds against her adult children come to light as her family arrives at her Oklahoma home after a relative dies.

507477.title: The Ghost Writer
507477.description: A writer agrees to author the memoirs of a former Prime Minister only to learn that he is a war criminal and that his first writer was found dead.

512252.title: We Need to Talk About Kevin
512252.description: In this suspenseful and gripping psychological thriller, a mother contends for years with the increasing malevolence of her first-born child, Kevin.

517750.title: The Conjuring
517750.description: Terrifying true story of a family attacked by paranormal, hostile events in their home in 1971, a disturbance only two paranormal experts could fix.

520213.title: Train to Busan (Dubbed)

521175.title: My Friend Dahmer
521175.description: Based on a graphic novel, the story of an awkward young Jeffrey Dahmer portrays the haunting struggle of a lonely high school boy who did not fit in.

524652.title: Coherence
524652.description: When eight friends gather for a dinner party on the night of an astronomical event, a series of unusual circumstances tests their relationships.

526368.title: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
526368.description: In this adaptation of Stieg Larsson's novel, hacker Lisbeth Salander teams up with a journalist to investigate a murder connected to a rich family.

526990.title: Re-Animator
526990.description: Cult horror-shocker about a medical student and his girlfriend who conduct outrageous experiments with dead tissue after a new student arrives.

534021.title: Stronger
534021.description: A man who was maimed by the Boston Marathon bombing, becoming a double amputee, helps police find the terrorists while trying to heal from trauma.

539677.title: Lion
539677.description: A young man makes an emotional journey to reconnect with his birth family in India after being tragically separated from them years earlier.

549640.title: Cartel Land
549640.description: A stark look at two Mexican drug cartel hot-spots and the two separate vigilante groups who've taken justice to eradicate crime into their own hands.

550636.title: The Void
550636.description: After Sheriff Deputy Carter finds an injured man on the side of the road, he takes him to a hospital where chaos and insanity break out.

551307.title: Audition
551307.description: In his search for a new wife, a widowed TV producer stages a dating service to screen women and finds one who isn't quite as perfect as her audition.

553005.title: We Are the Flesh (Español)

556634.title: Marina Abramovic: The Artist Is Present
556634.description: Get an intimate look at the Serbian conceptual and performance artist as she prepares for the 2010 retrospective of her work at New York’s MoMA.

556638.title: The Green Prince
556638.description: After retiring to the U.S., the Palestinian son of a founding leader of Hamas, voluntarily outs himself as a mole for the Israeli secret service.

566803.title: A Man Called Ove
566803.description: When a boisterous Persian family, including a pregnant woman, moves next door to the neighborhood’s grumpy old man, unexpected love and kinship bloom.

568448.title: The Night Eats the World
568448.description: What seems like a nightmare is a horrifying reality for a man who wakes up in Paris as apparently the only survivor of a swarm of killer zombies.

568896.title: Seven
568896.description: The final case for a retiring detective and his rookie partner follows a serial killer using the Bible’s seven deadly sins to target his victims.

579275.title: Hunt for the Wilderpeople
579275.description: Comic dynamite about a rebellious city kid who takes off with his gruff foster uncle in the New Zealand bush just as a manhunt begins to catch them.

579379.title: Super Dark Times
579379.description: Two teen boys and best friends see their calm suburban world implode after the accidental death of a classmate leads to another death they can’t hide.

579647.title: Fahrenheit 9/11
579647.description: The definitive exposé revealing how and why the Bush Administration manufactured evidence to invade war in Iraq following the 2001 terrorist attacks.

580530.title: Detroit
580530.description: This relevant, fact-based story, set in 1967’s Detroit riots, tracks a group of rogue cops, who respond to a call with vengeance instead of justice.

582027.title: Killing Them Softly
582027.description: When a duo of inept crooks are hired to rob a mob-run poker game and crush the local criminal economy, vengeance is sought via a reluctant hitman.

582081.title: Vicky Cristina Barcelona
582081.description: Two American women are taken in by the splendor of Spain, but not as much as they are drawn to a rugged painter and his sultry former lover.

585776.title: Burning
585776.description: A man agrees to watch an ex-neighbor’s cat while she goes on a trip and becomes suspicious of the man she brings back just before her disappearance.

588324.title: Professor Marston and the Wonder Women (En)
588324.description: Here’s the true origins story of a modern-day feminist superhero – Wonder Woman – and the psychologist-inventor who created the powerful character.

589091.title: American Animals
589091.description: The true story of four young men who feel their lives are like a movie and attempt to steal a rare and valuable book from a Kentucky University.

589111.title: The Lost Boys
589111.description: Sleep all day. Party all night. Never grow old. Never die. When a woman and her sons move to a California town, they discover the fun of vampire life.

589292.title: The Mask
589292.description: Jim Carrey’s superstar role as a kind and meek bank teller who gets super powers from a Nordic mask and becomes a totally s-s-s-smokin’ hero!

589490.title: Starfish
589490.description: Cassette tapes left behind by her dead BFF helps Aubrey navigate the apocalypse that arrived the day of the funeral when alien beasts attacked Earth.

589540.title: Thelma
589540.description: When a sexually repressed college student explores her feelings for her female friend, she unwittingly unleashes terrifying psychokinetic powers.

599086.title: The Third Wife
599086.description: After becoming the third wife to a wealthy landowner in 19th century Vietnam, May struggles with family and the prospects of motherhood.

602287.title: Princess Cyd
602287.description: A 16-year-old leaves her depressed father to visit her novelist aunt in Chicago over the summer, where she falls for a neighbor girl.

602506.title: Slither
602506.description: When an alien organism attacks a small town, a devoted wife must accept that her husband has transformed from the man she married.

602931.title: Howards End
602931.description: E.M. Forster's tale of a businessman who fights his wife's wishes to give their estate to another woman, illustrating stark class differences.

604500.title: Wargames
604500.description: Would you like to play a game? Computer hacker David Lightman (Matthew Broderick) can break the most intricate secret codes and master even the most difficult computer games. But when he unwittingly taps into the Defense Department's war computer, he initiates a confrontation of global proportions -- World War III. Together with his girlfriend (Ally Sheedy) and a computer genius (John Wood), David must race against time to outwit his opponent...and prevent a nuclear Armageddon!

614727.title: The Miseducation of Cameron Post
614727.description: Chloë Grace Moretz stars as a teen who bonds with other misunderstood LGBT youth when she is forced into gay conversion therapy by her guardians.

624927.title: Night of the Living Dead (In Color)
624927.description: A group of strangers struggles to fend off an attack of bloodthirsty zombies while barricading themselves inside a rural Pennsylvania farmhouse.

637111.title: ATL
637111.description: Inside an Atlanta roller rink, four hip hop-loving teens face life-changing turning points as they prepare for what comes next after high school.

637827.title: Don Jon
637827.description: A Jersey guy addicted to porn meets a charming and beautiful woman whom he hopes to pursue a real relationship with, but his habits get in the way.

640031.title: Blackfish
640031.description: Award-winning documentary about the ethics of taking killer whales captive, especially after a loving trainer’s public death in a Sea World enclosure.

640302.title: Giant Little Ones
640302.description: When two teenage best friends experience an unexpected incident on the night of a 17th birthday party, they watch as their lives change forever.

641484.title: Brown Sugar
641484.description: A record label producer and his longtime best friend come to the discovery that they’re in love almost immediately after one of them gets engaged.

642254.title: The Girl with All the Gifts
642254.description: In a bleak future, mankind has succumbed to a fungus that turns everyone into flesh-eating monsters, until an immune child is discovered.

643079.title: For a Few Dollars More
643079.description: In this classic, truly great spaghetti western, a keen, quick-witted bounty hunter and his fierce rival follow the bloody trail of a murderous outlaw.

643081.title: West Side Story
643081.description: This electrifying musical, winner of ten Academy Awards, including Best Picture, reimagines “Romeo and Juliet,” set during gang warfare in 1950s NYC.

644877.title: Rio Lobo
644877.description: Howard Hawks directs John Wayne in a Western about three ex-Civil War soldiers rallying the frontier to rebel against a corrupt and nasty sheriff.

646730.title: Fists of Fury
646730.description: A kung-fu fighter discovers the ice factory where he works is a front for the same drug trafficking ring responsible for the deaths of his relatives.

649963.title: Freaks
649963.description: A little girl who has been shut away from the outside world by her father soon discovers a dangerous universe awaiting beyond her front door.

652270.title: The Goonies
652270.description: A pair of brothers hope to save their house by following a treasure map and taking their friends along on a subterranean sea adventure.

653617.title: The Crying Game
653617.description: When British soldier Jody is kidnapped by the IRA, he befriends his captor, Fergus. Later, Fergus escapes to London where he encounters Jody's lover.

654055.title: The Jerk
654055.description: Steve Martin makes his film-starring debut in the wacky comedy hit The Jerk. From rags to riches... to rags, the laughter never stops!

658082.title: To Die For
658082.description: Suzanne is dead set on being a famous TV reporter. When her husband asks her to give up her dream, she plots against him with a love-struck teenager.

663814.title: The Sisters Brothers
663814.description: Brothers and assassins Eli and Charlie Sisters pursue a prospector across the American Northwest in this witty reimagining of the cinematic Western.

664742.title: Speed
664742.description: A city bus with a bomb aboard is set to explode if it falls under 50 mph. An L.A. officer must help one of the passengers steer the bus to safety.

664878.title: The Manchurian Candidate
664878.description: When a platoon of U.S. soldiers are captured during the Korean War, Major Bennett Marco discovers a diabolical plot involving enemy leaders.

667137.title: 12 Angry Men
667137.description: A fair-minded juror exposes holes in the prosecution's case to create a reasonable doubt and cast light on the biases that often pollute the system.

670407.title: The Fifth Element
670407.description: Director Luc Besson's extravagantly-styled, outrageous sci-fi tale of good against evil set in an unbelievable twenty-third century world.

673250.title: 1BR
673250.description: Leaving behind her painful past, Sarah scores the perfect Hollywood apartment only to discover that her welcoming neighbors may harbor a dark secret.

676660.title: The Babadook
676660.description: A mother struggles to protect her son from an evil supernatural entity that has escaped the pages of a children's book and is lurking in their home.

676665.title: The Death of Stalin
676665.description: Follows the wild scramble for power inside the Council of Ministers upon the sudden illness and death of Soviet dictator Joseph Stalin in 1953.

676725.title: Boyhood
676725.description: Richard Linklater's acclaimed hit, filmed over twelve years with the same cast, is a groundbreaking celebration of life, growing up, and parenting.

676860.title: Bone Tomahawk
676860.description: When a group of individuals kidnaps settlers from a small town, an unlikely team of gunslingers, led by Sheriff Hunt, sets out to bring them home.

680200.title: Lady Macbeth
680200.description: Lust, power, and murder collide in this thriller about the awakening of a young woman’s desire in rural England, 1865.

680865.title: Unforgiven
680865.description: After more than a decade living in peace a former gunslinger, lured by a huge bounty, regresses into the cold-blooded killer he once was.

681626.title: To the Stars
681626.description: Reclusive teen Iris endures the daily doses of bullying from her peers. She finds solace in Maggie, the charismatic and enigmatic new girl at school.

681750.title: Touching the Void
681750.description: An incredible account of tragedy and friendship, this film follows two men's thrilling and disastrous climb of the treacherous Siula Grande in Peru.

681752.title: The Snowtown Murders
681752.description: After a charismatic serial murderer befriends a troubled teen, he slowly seduces him into a darkly violent and unforgiving new world.

681773.title: Cold in July
681773.description: A brutal break-in triggers a downward spiral of lies and violence for a protective father and a murderous ex-con deep into the bloody heart of Texas.

682041.title: Mandy
682041.description: When a nightmarish cult attacks Red and Mandy, the shocking assault leads to a spiraling, surreal, bloody rampage of all-out, mind-altering vengeance.

682050.title: I Kill Giants
682050.description: Barbara Thorson, a young woman struggling with life, is the only thing that stands between terrible giants and the destruction of her small town.

682615.title: The Bourne Ultimatum
682615.description: Jason Bourne flees a new generation of skilled CIA operatives in a non-stop race around the globe while seeking the truth behind his mysterious past.

682626.title: Get Him to the Greek
682626.description: Aspiring music exec Aaron Green has just 72 hours to deliver rock legend Aldous Snow to LA, navigating a minefield of mayhem to get there.

682992.title: Charade
682992.description: Before she can finalize her divorce, Regina Lampert’s husband turns up dead and she soon finds herself pursued in Paris for the fortune he’d stolen.

683309.title: The Love Witch
683309.description: A modern-day witch in California uses spells and magic to get men to fall in love with her in this tribute to 1960’s Technicolor thrillers.

684099.title: Plus One
684099.description: Long-time friends Alice and Ben make an agreement to be one another's plus-ones as they power through an endless parade of insufferable weddings.

684120.title: Wildlife
684120.description: Family bonds are stretched to their breaking point after a teenage boy’s father leaves home to take a dangerous job against his mother's wishes.

684121.title: Weekend
684121.description: A drunken one-night stand morphs into a deeper, more intimate and exciting romance over the course of a booze, drug and sex-filled weekend.

684126.title: The Stanford Prison Experiment
684126.description: Based on the infamous true story, two dozen students role play as prisoners and guards in a terrifying experiment that shocked the world.

684140.title: Ghost Stories
684140.description: A skeptical professor devoted to debunking paranormal events falls into a world of terror while investigating a series of mysterious apparitions.

684149.title: Camp X-Ray
684149.description: A young Guantanamo prison guard forms an unlikely relationship with a longtime inmate in this riveting psychological drama.

684356.title: Bodied
684356.description: Follows a grad student on his accidental climb up the ranks as a politically-incorrect battle rapper in the merciless culture of poetic personal jabs.

684884.title: Don't Breathe

688929.title: In the Line of Fire
688929.description: The story of a man looking to redeem himself by saving the life of America's highest elected official, even if it means sacrificing himself.

689650.title: The Pink Panther
689650.description: The bumbling Inspector Jacques Clouseau tries to catch an infamous jewel thief before he can steal a priceless diamond from a princess.

689652.title: In the Heat of the Night
689652.description: While traveling in the deep south, a black Philadelphian homicide detective becomes embroiled in a murder investigation.

690261.title: Everything Must Go
690261.description: A salesman loses his wife and his job on the same day and, faced with his life imploding, begins living on his front lawn with all of his belongings.

694396.title: It
694396.description: In the town of Derry, Maine, seven young kids band together to stop a new killing cycle of an ancient, shape-shifting predator they can only call It.

694638.title: Nightmare Cinema
694638.description: The audience members at a haunted movie theater witness a series of screenings showing them their deepest fears and darkest secrets over five tales.

701940.title: American Violet
701940.description: In Texas, during the 2000 U.S. presidential election, a Black single mom fights to clear her name after being wrongfully arrested on drug charges.

707333.title: At Eternity's Gate
707333.description: Goes inside the world and the mind of Vincent van Gogh during his final years in Arles and Auvers-sur-Oise, France as his mental illness took hold.

711013.title: Mid90s
711013.description: A 13-year-old spends his summer navigating a troubled home life and skating with a crew of new friends.

711708.title: The Hole in the Ground
711708.description: A woman suspects that her son, who returned home after disappearing in the woods, is an imposter.

711709.title: American Honey
711709.description: An adolescent girl from a troubled home runs away with a traveling sales crew who drive across the American Midwest selling subscriptions door to door.

712866.title: Dog Soldiers
712866.description: Deep in the Scotland wilderness during a routine military exercise, British soldiers are plunged into a terrifying nightmare of unlikely enemies.

714948.title: Michael Collins
714948.description: One of Ireland's most controversial patriots and revolutionary heroes leads his countrymen in the early 20th century in their fight for independence.

720844.title: Dead Poets Society
720844.description: John Keating, a charismatic English professor, uses poetry to breathe new life into his students at a strict, all-boys prep school.

723626.title: Backcountry
723626.description: A romantic camping trip in the wilderness for a young couple devolves into a fight for survival as they face the dark side of nature in a hungry bear.

723812.title: Black '47
723812.description: In 1847 western Ireland at the height of the Potato Famine, one soldier goes on a ruthless pursuit of justice against those who murdered his family.

724340.title: The Autopsy of Jane Doe
724340.description: Coroners are mystified by an unidentified corpse until a series of terrifying events makes it clear that cadaver Jane Doe is not actually dead.

724377.title: Downfall
724377.description: Traudl Junge, the final secretary for Adolf Hitler, tells of the Nazi dictator's final days in his Berlin bunker at the end of World War II.

724420.title: The Way Back
724420.description: A band of convicts stages an escape from a World War II Siberian gulag and embarks on a 4,000-mile journey on foot across five countries to freedom.

724653.title: Baskin
724653.description: Five cops stumble upon the blood-spattered bowels of hell, where dark rituals and unspeakable horrors await in this head-spinning freakout.

724713.title: Blue Is the Warmest Color
724713.description: A young French student finds love and affection for the first time with a lover when she begins a passionate relationship with a free-spirited woman.

725431.title: Once Were Brothers: Robbie Robertson and the Band
725431.description: A story of a man overcoming adversity and finding camaraderie alongside those who’d become his brothers in one of history’s most enduring pop bands.

725799.title: The Last Mistress
725799.description: In this provocative romance, Vellini is a feisty Spanish mistress who will stop at nothing to be in the arms of her forbidden lover.

100000001.title: Kubo and the Two Strings
100000001.description: After accidentally summoning an evil spirit, Kubo must recover his fallen samurai father’s mystical weaponry and discover his own magical powers.

100000100.title: Room 237
100000100.description: Stanley Kubrick's classic film The Shining gets a riveting and in-depth exploration of its hidden meanings, dazzling puzzles and conspiracy theories.

100000218.title: The Secret in Their Eyes
100000218.description: A recently retired criminal court investigator writes a novel based on a twenty-five-year-old unresolved rape and murder case, which still haunts him.

100000270.description: Featuring a world-class ensemble cast, this gripping true-life thriller follows a spy gone rogue, who risks everything to stop an unjust war.

100000360.title: Young & Beautiful

100000441.title: Gremlins

100000941.title: Mary and Max

100001071.title: The Nightingale
100001071.description: A young Irish convict chases a British officer through the wilderness, bent on revenge for a terrible act of violence he committed against her family.

100001167.title: The Wind
100001167.description: Forces of nature tremble with an unseen evil in this chilling tale of madness, paranoia and supernatural terror howling across the Western frontier.

100001179.title: What Keeps You Alive
100001179.description: During a trip to an old family cabin in the mountains, one woman must survive her wife's twisted secret in this terrifying cat-and-mouse thriller.

100001338.title: The Survivalist
100001338.description: After a deadly apocalypse, two hungry women come upon a survivalist who grows his own vegetables, making a dangerous bargain in exchange for food.

100001390.title: Tale of Tales
100001390.description: This inventive anthology film brings us three gory, gorgeous, grown-up stories of magic, monsters, and royalty based on Italian fairy tales.

100001413.title: Matchstick Men
100001413.description: The streetwise teen daughter he never knew existed suddenly turns a neurotic con artist’s two-man team in small-time crime into a family business.

100001495.title: Eight Below

100001602.title: Godzilla

100002112.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 1
100002112.description: After waking up from a four-year coma, a former assassin seeks revenge on the team of killers that betrayed her—and that she was once a part of.

100002113.title: Jackie Brown
100002113.description: Female flight attendant Jackie Brown becomes a key figure in a plot between the federal authorities and her street-tough arms dealer boss.

100002156.title: Men in Black
100002156.description: Tasked with policing extraterrestrial activities on Earth, two agents join forces to track down a dangerous alien intent upon galactic destruction.

100002159.title: Kill Bill: Vol. 2
100002159.description: The Bride continues her quest for revenge, fighting her way through a host of assassins in pursuit of a final showdown with the man who betrayed her.
